# ─── DEVELOPMENT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Target used by the Vite dev proxy for /api/* during `npm run dev`.
# Only read at dev-server startup; not inlined into the production bundle.
VITE_API_TARGET="http://localhost:4000"

# ─── PRODUCTION ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Full origin + path the built app calls in the browser. Must include the
# firm-scoped portal prefix on the backend. Example for the seeded dev firm:
#   https://api.counselintake.com/firms/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/portal
#
# Leave unset in local dev — src/config.ts falls back to "/api" and Vite's
# proxy handles the rewrite. In Vercel, set this in Project → Settings →
# Environment Variables for the Production environment.
VITE_API_BASE=""
